JOHANNESBURG - The SAPS in Gauteng is launching the provincial safer festive season operations. Police Minister Bheki Cele and Police Commissioner Kehla Sitole are attending the launch. READ: 80 arrested in Joburg police raids The SAPS will raid derelict buildings in the CBD, erect roadblocks and conduct sting operations on counterfeit and second-hand goods. The team of police officers on Friday morning travelled from Hillbrow through Johannesburg, conducting raids. READ: Police raid multi-million rand drug labs in Gauteng, Mpumalanga In Hillbrow, foreign nationals without documentation were detained by the police. The police travelled on the train and heard the challenges commuters face on public transport, including theft and violence.